    tickets = zenpy_client.views.tickets(int(view_id))
    payload = []
    for ticket in tickets:
        aux = {""id"": ticket.id,
               ""status"":ticket.status,
               ""satisfaction"":ticket.satisfaction_rating,
               ""subject"": ticket.subject,
               ""requester"":ticket.requester_id,
               ""request_date"":ticket.created_at,
               ""updated_dates"":ticket.updated_at,
               ""channel"":ticket.via.channel,
               ""tag"":ticket.tags,
               ""type"":ticket.type,
               ""last_comment"":ticket.description
              }
        payload.append(aux)
    return payload`


I have seen this in a Zendesk community post, but it doesn't seem to work if I do ticket.dates:
https://support.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/community/posts/115000867608-Need-Solved-Date-information-
{  
   ""ticket"":{  
      ...
      ""dates"":{  
         ""assignee_updated_at"":""2017-02-07T14:01:23Z"",
         ""requester_updated_at"":""2017-02-07T13:59:55Z"",
         ""status_updated_at"":""2017-03-08T08:01:50Z"",
         ""initially_assigned_at"":""2017-02-07T13:59:55Z"",
         ""assigned_at"":""2017-02-07T13:59:55Z"",
         ""solved_at"":""2017-02-07T14:01:23Z"",
         ""latest_comment_added_at"":""2017-02-07T14:01:18Z""
      },
      ...
   }
}

Thanks Pierre-Philippe",{},{}
