2397,IssuesEvent,2016-07-05 18:28:10+00:00,46906439,diafygi/acme-tiny,643187,diafygi,,,closed,Add branches to make contributing easier,[],[],5,"Right now the only branch is master, and since users clone directly from that branch PRs can't be merged until they're production-ready. This can make it difficult for contributors, particularly when multiple people contribute to the new feature (example: #59). The normal solution for this would be adding branches.

My suggestion would be adding development branch where mainline development can be performed, then also create new branches off that for each new feature that isn't ready to be merged. So small PRs can be immediately merged into the development branch, and bigger PRs can get their own branch until it's ready for testing.

This also works well with the addition of setup.py, since that will allow you to tag releases in the master branch without having to worry about any of the unfinished code.",{},{}
