And if things work, I'd be happy to update the docs.

Thanks for your help
Juergen ",{},{}
2489,IssuesEvent,2018-03-12 09:56:32+00:00,78549488,flomotlik/formica,132653,flomotlik,,,closed,Add option to push Template to S3 before deployment,"[{'id': 515382397, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/flomotlik/formica/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],0,"When templates become too large they have to be pushed into S3 first before deployment. We have to give an option to make this possible so users can deploy through S3.

`--s3-path BUCKET_PATH_AND_FOLDER`

```
formica change --stack something --s3-path bucketname/something/whatever
```

It will automatically create a file named

`STACK_NAME-TIMESTAMP.template.json`",{},{}
