2823,IssuesEvent,2018-04-26 20:36:10+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,136959,Mottie,,,closed,Don't use the jQuery variable but the local $ one,"[{'id': 153146, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Mottie/tablesorter/labels/Bug', 'name': 'Bug', 'color': 'e11d21', 'default': False}, {'id': 30749346, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Mottie/tablesorter/labels/Widget', 'name': 'Widget', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}, {'id': 240570354, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Mottie/tablesorter/labels/Widget-Build', 'name': 'Widget-Build', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}]",[],1,"The file [widget-build-table.js](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/200fcacb3bc1a09be3c953932275aa52c3bd7b2f/js/widgets/widget-build-table.js) (and maybe others, I only checked this one) uses an IIFE with `jQuery` as a parameter mapped to `$` but still uses `jQuery` instead of `$` inside of the code base. This makes the code break if a subsequent script uses `jQuery.noConflict()`.

Changing all occurrences of `jQuery` except for the IIFE param to `$` fixes the issue.",{},{}
2830,IssuesEvent,2015-03-25 15:43:33+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,136959,Mottie,,,closed,Use background-color instead of background for hovered rows,[],[],1,"In the css for hovered rows (eg theme.blue.css lines 107 and 113, or I guess .evenHovered and .oddHovered in theme.less), the background color of the row is set using ""background"". An unfortunate side-effect of this is other background properties (eg background-image, background-repeat, etc) are set to none. This makes it very difficult to use a background image in a table cell via css, as the selector used in the theme is quite specific, and so normally wins (using !important does work to set the background image, but I would rather not if possible).

I can't see any reason not to use just background-color in the theme file, rather than background. Any change of making that change?

thanks,
Stuart
",{},{}
