3081,IssuesEvent,2015-05-01 04:16:20+00:00,5806020,rueckstiess/mtools,243499,victorhooi,,,opened,"mlaunch should print error message for invalid options, rather than silently ignoring",[],[],0,"Currently, `mlaunch` will silently ignore any invalid options that you attempt to pass through. For example, the following will not produce any syntax errors:
```
mlaunch init --single --carrots --apples
```

I understand that we will need to check both `mongos` and `mongod` for what is a valid option - however, it would be nice to error out for invalid syntax - otherwise a user may assume something works (e.g. setting storage engine to WiredTiger) when they actually mis-spelt it, and it did not work.",{},{}
