3899,IssuesEvent,2017-05-14 14:50:06+00:00,90407498,jbasko/configmanager,632910,jbasko,,,closed,Config section class?,"[{'id': 604760895, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jbasko/configmanager/labels/design-stage', 'name': 'design-stage', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Facts:

 * Represents a container of config items and other config sections.
 * Very little to do with `ConfigParser`'s section -- we support arbitrary depth config, but ConfigParser only supports two levels and sections are the top layer.

Discussion:

 * Section does not have to have a name -- main application config section probably won't have one
 * Section may have a name if the section was auto-created, no?
 * When composing a section, should be able to rename a section.

 * [ ] `.add()` - add a config item or a sub-section to this section. This must not change anything inside the added object. This must not copy the object (unlike `ConfigManager.add()` does at the moment)
 * [ ] `.get(name, fallback=not_set)` -- does it get value or item/section?
 * [ ] `.set(name, value)` -- `.set(item, value)` ??
 * [ ] `.has(name)` -- `.has(item)` ??
 * [ ] `.iter_sections(recursive=False)`
 * [ ] `.iter_items(recursive=False)`
 * [ ] `.iter_children(recursive=False)` -- iterate over both, sections and items

```
logging_config = ConfigSection('logging', {
    'version': 1,
    'disable_existing_loggers': False,
    'formatters': {
        'standard': {
            'format': '%(asctime)s [%(levelname)s] %(name)s: %(message)s'
        },
    },
    'handlers': {
        'default': {
            'level': 'INFO',
            'formatter': 'standard',
            'class': 'logging.StreamHandler',
        },
    },
    'loggers': {
        '': {
            'handlers': ['default'],
            'level': 'INFO',
            'propagate': True,
        },
    },
})

app_config = ConfigSection({
    'logging': logging_config,
})
```


### Section Rename Example

```
# uploads.py
config = ConfigSection('main', {
    'threads': 1
})
assert config.main.threads.value == 1

# app.py
from .uploads import config as uploads_config
config = ConfigSection('main', {
    'greeting': 'Hello!',
    'uploads': uploads_config,
})
assert config.main.greeting.value == 'Hello'
assert config.uploads.threads.value == 1
```

### Accessing Sub-Sections in Raw Format

With the logging config as above, what if user wants to access the entire `logging.handlers.default` block as one mutable variable?

```
# BAD IDEA
assert isinstance(config.logging.handlers.raw, list)
assert isinstance(config.logging.handlers.default.raw, dict)
```


",{},{}
