@architect.install('partition', type='range', subtype='date', constraint='month', column='time_received', db=config.database.engine)

Then I run:
architect partition -m core.db.models,  it returns success.

Then, when I start inserting rows from sqlalchemy, architect it creates the right tables but I find my rows in the parent and also the child table, they should be available only in my child tables.

Do you know why ?

Thanks !",{},{}
4122,IssuesEvent,2017-02-09 19:54:31+00:00,120894,michaeljones/breathe,3090295,AWhetter,,,opened,Split node traversal from SphinxRenderer into a base class,[],[],0,"I'm using breathe to parse doxygen xml files but I need to generate different types of nodes other than Sphinx nodes. Because SphinxRenderer is doing both node traversal and rendering it's difficult to inherit from the class and use it only for traversal. I'm having to copy over so much code that it isn't really worth me inheriting from SphinxRenderer.
