4147,IssuesEvent,2017-11-15 23:27:55+00:00,6054289,niklasf/python-chess,402777,niklasf,,,closed,The SVG chessboard does not have any animation,[],[],1,"The current state of the SVG chessboard is that it's a static SVG image. It would be wonderful if someone would implement drag&drop or click&click behaviour for the pieces so that they can be moved on the SVG chessboard.

I was inspecting the SVG code that is produced by `chess.svg.board` function and found in Google Chrome an `SVGElement` property collection that holds this properties `onclick`, `ondrag`, `ondrop`. After clicking on the three dots in either `onclick: (...)`, `ondrag: (...)` or `ondrop: (...)` threw an
