4338,IssuesEvent,2016-12-19 11:29:08+00:00,37154906,fboender/ansible-cmdb,4283875,crisvp,,,opened,"When failing due to a templating error, the error message is unclear and ansible does not exit with a non-zero status code",[],[],0,"When it encounters a KeyError while processing it reports the failure as ""address"".

```
> ansible-cmdb -t ./keyerror.tpl -i production/inventory /tmp/fnord
Whoops, it looks like something went wrong while rendering the template.

The reported error was: 'address'

The output is probably not correct.
You can re-run ansible-cmdb with the -d switch to turn on debugging
to get an insight in what might be going wrong:

  /usr/local/bin/ansible-cmdb -d -t ./html_servicedesk.tpl -i production/inventory /tmp/fnord

You can report a bug on the issue tracker:

  https://github.com/fboender/ansible-cmdb/issues

Please include the debugging output (-d switch) in the report!

If you can, also include the hosts file and the facts file for the last host
that rendered properly ('Rendering host...' in the output. If these files must
remain confidential, you can send them to ferry.boender@gmail.com instead.
> echo $?
0
```

The process then exits with a zero exit-status, instead of the expected non-zero status.

Under different circumstances the message appears missing entirely:

```
> ansible-cmdb -d -t ./blankerror.tpl -i production/inventory /tmp/fnord
\data_dir = /usr/local/Cellar/ansible-cmdb/1.18/ansiblecmdb/data
tpl_dir = /usr/local/Cellar/ansible-cmdb/1.18/ansiblecmdb/data/tpl
static_dir = /usr/local/Cellar/ansible-cmdb/1.18/ansiblecmdb/data/static
config_file = None
inventory hostfile = production/inventory
Parsing fact dir: /tmp/fnord
Reading host facts from {bunch of hosts}
Parsing host vars (dir): production/inventory
template file = ./blankerror.tpl
Template params: {'lib_dir': '/usr/local/Cellar/ansible-cmdb/1.18/ansiblecmdb/data', 'version': '1.18', 'data_dir': '/usr/local/Cellar/ansible-cmdb/1.18/ansiblecmdb/data', 'log': <logging.RootLogger object at 0x10287c890>, 'columns': None}
















> echo $?
0
```

Again, with zero exit status.


Tested on ansible-cmdb 1.18 on MacOS.
The (obviously broken) template files are attached.

[blankerror.tpl.txt](https://github.com/fboender/ansible-cmdb/files/660884/blankerror.tpl.txt)
[keyerror.tpl.txt](https://github.com/fboender/ansible-cmdb/files/660885/keyerror.tpl.txt)

",{},{}
