5050,IssuesEvent,2015-01-20 14:16:35+00:00,9376661,lorenzofox3/Smart-Table,10614404,mremmik,,,opened,st-search does not trim input,[],[],0,"Angular by default automatically trims whitespace from around values of input fields bound to a model, so that entering 'foo' or '       foo ' will both result in the bound variable to be nicely set to 'foo'.

It appears that input fields that are decorated for st-search for search functionality do not trim input, so searching for ' foo' instead of 'foo', eg from copy-pasting the search term from somewhere, does not find 'foo' or 'foobar' or so forth.

It would be nice for usability to have st-search to automatically trim the input. For people who do a lot of copy-pasting, the lack of it can be a deal-breaker.",{},{}
