6057,IssuesEvent,2015-01-08 17:58:19+00:00,24038919,eyeseast/python-frontmatter,25778,eyeseast,,,opened,Allow user to pass in YAML keyword args in frontmatter.dump and frontmatter.dumps,[],[],0,"Based on discussion in #9. This would allow a user to export metadata beyond the default types supported by PyYAML, including `set` and `OrderedDict` types. It would also allow better processors, like [pretty-yaml](https://github.com/mk-fg/pretty-yaml).

Proposed usage:

```python
>>> import pyaml
>>> post = frontmatter.loads(text, title=""Hello, World"")
>>> frontmatter.dumps(post, Dumper=pyaml.PrettyYAMLDumper)
```

Both `dump` and `dumps` need to accept arbitrary keyword arguments, and pass those along to `yaml.dump` (instead of `yaml.safe_dump`, as currently used).

The `Dumper` argument should default to `yaml.SafeDumper` or `yaml.CSafeDumper`. Override that at your own risk.",{},{}
