When I build MXNet from source using same build flags as pip package uses, I get much faster speeds. Not sure which versions of dependencies could be different in our case. I used all standard dependencies versions that come with AWS Deep Learning AMI (Cuda 9, CUDNN 7005). This could be because of the OpenCV version used to build. Happy to provide any information needed on this front.

Here is a comparison of running Resnet50v1 on the Imagenet dataset using 8 V100s on a p3.16xl machine with 2048 batch size fp16, all else being equal.

**Built from source: ~5200 samples/sec
Nightly pip package mxnet-cu90: ~3500 samples/sec**

