7851,IssuesEvent,2017-11-14 23:25:44+00:00,648332,assimp/assimp,5471254,awefers,265533,assimp,opened,glTF2 import: Transforms are incorrect (patch attached),[],[],0,"Transforms are incorrect when importing a glTF 2.0 file with a decomposed node transform (translation,  rotation and scale). This is happening because the multiplication order is not to spec, from the glTF 2.0 spec (https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF/tree/master/specification/2.0):

""TRS properties are converted to matrices and postmultiplied in the T * R * S order to compose the transformation matrix; first the scale is applied to the vertices, then the rotation, and then the translation.""

You can observe the issue when trying to import ""Project Polly"" from ""https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF-Blender-Exporter/tree/master/polly"". The card box, the name plaque and the styrofoam piece will be in the wrong place.

 I have attached  a patch that fixes the transform calculation.

[gltf2_transform_fix.patch.zip](https://github.com/assimp/assimp/files/1472887/gltf2_transform_fix.patch.zip)
",{},{}
