8560,IssuesEvent,2018-05-01 23:43:24+00:00,79510167,pypa/pipenv,9513968,gtalarico,647025,pypa,opened,Feature: Add active environment name to PROMPT Var,[],[],0,"On unix/fish, when a shell is started using `pipenv shell`, the `$VIRTUAL_ENV` variable can be used to provide a visual indicator on the shell. For Example, if the users prompt is ` (~/folder)  $`
once the shell using `pipenv shell` and his prompt becomes:
` (~/folder) (pipenvfolder-1234) $`
or similar. This currently works well with zsh/fish, etc and in general in the unix world is fairly easy to customze the prompt.

On windows however, the `%PROMPT% variable is used instead, and this variable is used by both cmd.exe ad cmder console to add the virtual enviroment to the user's prompt by default.

Upon activating an environment, the environment name is prepended to the `$PROMPT` var.
As far as I know, this is not customizable on cmd.exe, and is not easilly customizable with cmder neither.

### cmd.exe behavior with virtualenv / virtualenv-wrapper
Active Enviroment is shown on prompt

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9513968/39497845-16d6f64e-4d73-11e8-88c8-603a3c08457b.png)

### cmder behavior with virtualenv  / virtualenv-wrapper
Active Enviroment is shown on prompt

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9513968/39497992-b03a709a-4d73-11e8-91cf-e825f7124a30.png)

### cmd and cmder with pipenv shell - No prompt indicator
Enviroment IS NOT shown anywhere on the prompt

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9513968/39498041-f412e612-4d73-11e8-8892-54bc396bb2b2.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9513968/39498029-e8ae26a6-4d73-11e8-9e41-d2eaf806bd13.png)


# Proposed solution

For the pipenv environemnt to be showm by default on the built in cmd.exe and other windows friendly console,  pipenv could prepend the shell enviroment name to the PROMPT variable, in the same way virtualenv already does.

Virtualenv stores that old prompt in `_OLD_VIRTUAL_PROMPT` so it can restore the original on deactivate, but pipenv would not need that since the process is destroyed.

### Working example on cmd.exe
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9513968/39498612-1264961c-4d77-11e8-9cf3-205b1e0e36f6.png)

### Working example on cmder
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9513968/39498523-9a008fdc-4d76-11e8-8e70-b2870d280fa1.png)

I would be happy to work on a PR if the proposal is accepted.



",{},{}
