8961,IssuesEvent,2017-08-04 12:41:09+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,19578852,mptorr,897180,scikit-image,closed,How can I determine the number of windows generated by view_as_windows?,[],[],3,"I'm trying to write a function that would provide me the number of windows output by `view_as_windows`, given the dimesions of _arr_in, window_shape, step_.

In a simple experiment using one grayscale image that is 256 x 256 I see that:

```
-- window_shape = (64, 64); step=64 generates this output
(4, 4, 64, 64) — 16 windows

-- window_shape = (64, 64); step=32 generates this output
(7, 7, 64, 64) — 49 windows

-- window_shape = (64, 64); step=16 generates this output
(13, 13, 64, 64) — 169 windows

-- window_shape = (64, 64); step=8 generates this output
(25, 25, 64, 64) — 625 windows

-- window_shape = (64, 64); step=4 generates this output
(49, 49, 64, 64) — 2,401 windows

-- window_shape = (64, 64); step=2 generates this output
(97, 97, 64, 64) — 9,409 windows

-- window_shape = (64, 64); step=1 generates this output
(193, 193, 64, 64) — 37,294 windows
```

[The documentation gives an example based on a 3D matrix](http://scikit-image.org/docs/dev/api/skimage.util.html#skimage.util.view_as_windows), but I wonder I anyone has a similar formula that could estimate the number of windows generated on a 2D example as above (other than simply multiplying the first 2 dimensions of the output matrix).
",{},{}
8994,IssuesEvent,2017-11-23 20:46:57+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,7454015,glemaitre,897180,scikit-image,closed,[RFC] CI tests examples in travis,[],[],2,"Isn't an overkill to always run the examples for all travis build.
When building the documentation, sphinx-gallery will anyway run the different examples and this build will fail for sure if there is any issue the same way that the other builds are failing nowadays.
It would also reduce the testing time I think on the CI. And it would also avoid some issue with the requirement as discussed at https://github.com/scikit-image/scikit-image/pull/2848#issuecomment-346581618

WDYT?",{},{}
9007,IssuesEvent,2016-04-02 03:11:48+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,1315589,soupault,897180,scikit-image,closed,Add Issue templates and declutter root directory,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-image/scikit-image/labels/maintenance', 'name': 'maintenance', 'color': '3d8bbf'}]",[],4,"GitHub [now supports a `.github/` directory for their new Issue/PR templates](https://github.com/blog/2111-issue-and-pull-request-templates). There are common enough things we should know in essentially all Issues we should probably enable the Issue template requesting Python version, scikit-image version, and ensure full tracebacks are included if available.

We should also move `CONTRIBUTING.txt` into that directory, decluttering the root. It's always been less than ideal having `CONTRIBUTORS.txt` and `CONTRIBUTING.txt` right next to each other.

These are easy, quality-of-life changes which do not need to go in before 0.12.",{},{}
