9085,IssuesEvent,2016-07-14 16:40:49+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,15566,rhyolight,1039191,numenta,closed,Vagrant instructions are out of date,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/newbie', 'name': 'newbie', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/status:help%20wanted', 'name': 'status:help wanted', 'color': 'fbca04'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/type:platform', 'name': 'type:platform', 'color': '006b75'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic/labels/wiki', 'name': 'wiki', 'color': '207de5'}]",[],4,"Following instructions at https://github.com/numenta/nupic/wiki/Running-NuPIC-in-a-Virtual-Machine will no longer yield a workable nupic installation.

Of note:
- [ ] there needs to be instructions supporting the `git submodule` dependency on nupic.core
- [ ] cmake is not installed in the image
- [ ] `yum install cmake` installs cmake 2.6, which is not compatible with nupic
- [ ] even after installing cmake 2.8 (via `sudo yum install cmake28.x86_64`) `cmake28 ..` inside `build_system/` fails (possibly because of numpy, see below).

To be current with nupic status quo, image needs to be updated to include the right version of cmake, python dependencies, and an updated default python 2.7 installation.  Instructions need to be revised, too.

