9229,IssuesEvent,2016-07-19 10:29:17+00:00,41366906,ImmobilienScout24/afp-cli,1067460,matey-jack,1132872,ImmobilienScout24,opened,afp write: Notify user about expiring credentials + easy way to get fresh ones,[],[],0,"I am mostly using ""afp write"" since I need credentials in my IDE and several open shell windows. Often commands (such as DataWario) fail late when there are expired credentials, so I want to avoid that situation.

I am currently working[1] on a small feature which uses python TK (TKinter) to show a count-down of validity for credentials in a small window which I can place whereever I want on my screen. The window shall have:
 - a display of remaining time in minutes (with red background when the time is < 5 minutes)
 - a button to delete credentials from .aws (end session)
 - a button to get fresh credentials to write to .aws (prolong session)

I am adding this issue so anyone can give feedback before I spend too much time on it.

Also, I only test on Ubuntu and would be happy about people testing it on Mac (and possibly further OS's).

[1] https://github.com/matey-jack",{},{}
9245,IssuesEvent,2016-07-04 14:56:33+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,189798,jirikuncar,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,accounts: delete account feature,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebAccess', 'name': 'c_WebAccess', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/master', 'name': 'master', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],5,"**Goal:**
Allow users to delete their account via the account settings.

**Additional info**
The account deletion facility should check any attached baskets, any predefined alerts, any submitted records, messages etc.

Overlays must be able to hook into the deletion process, to do custom processing via e.g. pre/post delete signals.

**Open questions:**
Do we delete the account or simply mark it as deleted for record keeping? 

See also issue #1973 ",{},{}
9261,IssuesEvent,2015-03-26 08:24:00+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,119349,kaplun,1157480,inveniosoftware,reopened,Generic LibX toolbar,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_installation', 'name': 'c_installation', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/r_wontfix', 'name': 'r_wontfix', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/s_CDS', 'name': 's_CDS', 'color': '4D94CE'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],2,"Originally on 2011-03-03

Today a LibX toolbar is available for CDS users:

http://libx.org/editions/download.php?edition=4F46CD81

LibX toolbar need to be customized for a particular repository. It would be nice to provide a default Invenio based LibX toolbar that can be quickly cloned and customized by simply providing the URL of the installation of Invenio.

This would require enriching the INSTALL guide of Invenio to advertize the URL of such Invenio LibX toolbar and to commit the 
```
invenio_search_implementation.js
