file into Invenio GIT.",{},{}
9268,IssuesEvent,2015-09-22 12:44:53+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,517546,tiborsimko,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,BibRank: take advantage of affected fields,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_BibRank', 'name': 'c_BibRank', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/legacy', 'name': 'legacy', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_major', 'name': 'p_major', 'color': 'e11d21'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],3,"Originally on 2013-11-19

Similarly to the record indexer, see #1573, it would be good to
take advantage of records' affected fields to see if BibRank daemon
has to really run on a given modified record or not.  Example: when
only title field was changed, it should not be necessary to trigger
citation re-indexing of the record.",{},{}
9273,IssuesEvent,2015-02-06 14:41:04+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,7428769,sbujam,1157480,inveniosoftware,opened,Introduction of url redirection for records moved to external sites.,[],[],0,"In addition to the work already done for merged records (that handles redirection from merged bibno -> new bibno **within** Invenio), it would be nice If a librarian could somehow define a redirection to an **external** url for a record that has been permanently deleted.

This would seem useful if for example one moves some records (or an entire collection) from one invenio site to another and wants to help users that have kept bookmarks of the old url location, find the new one.

A special 980 tag ""MOVED"" could be used (with similar functionality to ""DELETED""), that could also hold the redirection url, along with an optional message.
People who search for this record (via websearch, OAI, API, etc) would get for example a ""Record deleted and moved to XXXX. Please update your bookmarks."" along with the optional message.
",{},{}
9276,IssuesEvent,2015-09-22 13:00:30+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,517546,tiborsimko,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,BibSched: monitor termination after timeout,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_BibSched', 'name': 'c_BibSched', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/legacy', 'name': 'legacy', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_minor', 'name': 'p_minor', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_bug', 'name': 't_bug', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],1,"Originally on 2013-04-04

The bibsched monitor is basically always started via an *SSH* connection. If this drops (and the admin has not used tools such as `screen`, the bibsched process will stay there running idle forever (consuming SQL connection and resources).

It would be nice if there was a timeout (e.g. 24 hours) after which, if no key is pressed, the monitor terminates on its own.",{},{}
9280,IssuesEvent,2018-02-27 16:39:18+00:00,43819930,inveniosoftware/invenio-db,4835412,switowski,1157480,inveniosoftware,opened,pymysql 0.8 and binary_prefix,[],[],0,"With the 0.8 version of `pymysql`, travis builds that use MySQL will start failing, for example this build of invenio-files-rest:
https://travis-ci.org/switowski/invenio-files-rest/jobs/346369793

The enigmatic `<Result StatementError('(exceptions.ValueError) bytes is not a 16-char string',)>.exit_code` error seems to be caused by an update of pymysql, that is introducing a backward incompatible change: https://github.com/PyMySQL/PyMySQL/commit/4ff1bbcbacf92033ef922319d8fde11f8aa533e3

We can restore our previous behaviour by setting the `binary_prefix = True` in the connection parameters of the `pymysql`.
I will submit a PR shortly.",{},{}
