9320,IssuesEvent,2015-11-19 09:49:17+00:00,39133678,inveniosoftware/invenio-pidstore,1698163,lnielsen,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,circular dependency in registry.py,[],[],0,"This non-elegant solution in [registry.py:_collect_pidproviders](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-pidstore/pull/18/files#diff-eb450227ab35e98bf2e7ff84b846363dR34) is due to circular dependency between [provider.py](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-pidstore/pull/18/files#diff-49fc39ba80404dbb8a11560070f4ec0cR24) and [registry.py](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-pidstore/pull/18/files#diff-eb450227ab35e98bf2e7ff84b846363dR34)

One of the solutions might be removing the ``if not issubclass(provider, PidProvider)`` check, and catching it or letting it fail later in [provider.py:PidProvider.create](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-pidstore/pull/18/files#diff-49fc39ba80404dbb8a11560070f4ec0cL105).",{},{}
9324,IssuesEvent,2016-11-08 15:51:42+00:00,39133678,inveniosoftware/invenio-pidstore,189798,jirikuncar,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,RFC Report number minting,[],[],16,"### Proposal

Generic minter for report numbers with auto-increment per custom prefix.
### Examples

From what I can see on CDS, we have two patterns, the most common: ATLAS-COM-2015-001, ATLAS-COM-2015-002, etc. (this is straightforward, we have a prefix (""ATLAS-COM""), year and counter; the only thing that changes is the counter), and the less common variations of the previous version: CERN/SPC/0070/Draft, etc.
So having report number patterns like PREFIX + COUNTER + SUFFIX should work.
@ludmilamarian , @egabancho can you think of some report numbers that won't fit into that pattern ?

TODO
### Questions
- Shall this functionality live in this repo or shall we create new `invenio-pidstore-reportnumber` repo?
- How do we store the report numbers:
  - We create one table in DB and each ""report number type"" is a separate row. Those could be the fields:
    `id`, `prefix`, `suffix` and `counter`. The downside of this is that you don't keep the track of all report numbers created. So when there are some holes, because someone has minted a report number but never used it, we can't reuse that number.
  - If we want to keep track of each report number we have generated, we can either create a one DB table and store all minted report numbers in separate rows or create separate tables for different report number formats. With this approach we can also add recordID to each report number that was assigned to a record. This would allow to reuse report numbers that were minted but not assigned to a record, for example, if after 1 month report number was not used, we give it to the next person that mints report number from this category. This would be useful for people who really want to avoid ""holes"" in the report numbers (""why there is a report number 123 and 125 but not 124 ?!!!""), but I'm afraid that keeping tracks of used report numbers and reusing them will only bring us pain and misery.

[Edited by @switowski]
",{},{}
