9515,IssuesEvent,2016-03-05 01:20:06+00:00,15958352,GetBlimp/django-rest-framework-jwt,8824814,resalisbury,1227237,GetBlimp,opened,Different JWT_AUTH settings by app,[],[],0,"Right now, there is no easy way to have different `JWT_AUTH` settings for different django apps. 

For example, I have 2 apps:

 - internal_api
 - external_api

They need different settings for the expiration delta of a JWT token.

internal_api needs settings of:
```
    JWT_AUTH = {
        'JWT_EXPIRATION_DELTA': datetime.timedelta(hours=12),
    }```
external_api needs settings of:
```
    JWT_AUTH = {
        'JWT_EXPIRATION_DELTA': datetime.timedelta(seconds=300),
    } 
```

The only way I can figure out to do this now is to override `jwt_payload_handler` and then incorporate that override into a custom `ObtainJSONWebToken`.  Would also need to write a custom `RefreshJSONWebTokenSerializer.validate` to make sure the token can be refreshed, when using refresh tokens.   ",{},{}
9525,IssuesEvent,2015-08-26 12:19:14+00:00,10472606,qubole/qds-sdk-py,260107,kaneda,1259448,qubole,opened,Timeout is hard coded in connection wrapper,[],[],0,Timeout for net calls is hard coded to 300 seconds in https://github.com/qubole/qds-sdk-py/blob/master/qds_sdk/connection.py . This should be an option that is passed as part of params (and so on through https://github.com/qubole/qds-sdk-py/blob/master/qds_sdk/commands.py ) to allow a client to execute requests with variable timeout.,{},{}
