9938,IssuesEvent,2015-04-07 01:23:22+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,1454906,rmandelb,1462196,GalSim-developers,closed,New SEDs for WFIRST module,[],[],6,The SEDs currently available in GalSim (galsim/data/) go only up to 1200 nm. This hardly covers the first two of the many bandpass filters of the WFIRST. We need SEDs that go up to at least 2200 nm for the WFIRST module (#590),{},{}
9962,IssuesEvent,2015-09-03 19:00:35+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,3650485,jmeyers314,1462196,GalSim-developers,opened,Separable ChromaticObject with null SED at bandpass effective wavelength is undrawable.,[],[],0,"Drawing separable `ChromaticObject`s currently works by first drawing the achromatic object at the effective wavelength of the filter in question, and then scaling this image by the wavelength integral of bandpass * SED.  This fails, however, if the value of the SED is zero at the effective wavelength of the filter, a situation that probably doesn't occur too often with realistic spectra/filters but can occur (and just did for my office-mate!) for contrived tophat filters and SEDs.

One possible solution would be to search for a fiducial wavelength (probably still starting at the filter effective wavelength, or maybe at the midpoint between the filter blue/red edges) for which the SED has non-zero flux.",{},{}
