10057,IssuesEvent,2017-01-18 17:41:04+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,956898,jrowellfx,1505683,FortAwesome,opened,Icon Request: apple-fruit,[],[],0,"I need a symbol for an apple in a latex document I am writing, the only apple icon I could find was here in fontawesome, which is indeed awesome, however, it's the apple logo for the company. I'm using it for now, the document is private so for now it doesn't matter that it's the company logo.

I was thinking that a general (and small) set of fruit icons might be useful.  If you go onto google docs, on windows and insert the symbol for ""apple"" (it's missing on linux, and shaded/colored on the mac! - totally inconsistent across platforms, so you need to see it on a PC - oh well) you can see the kind of icon that might be useful.

In addition, it might also be useful to have a couple of other really typical fruit items.  Like banana-fruit, cherry-fruit, pineapple-fruit - as in the kind of things you might see on a slot-machine?

Anyway, thanks so much - just throwing this out there for your consideration.  Thanks again!",{},{}
10059,IssuesEvent,2018-06-28 08:04:59+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,556268,tagliala,1505683,FortAwesome,closed,Icon request: icon-name Responsive Web Design,[],[],1,"### What can it be used for?

Hey there! First time doing this, so if what I'm doing/asking for is not the right way to go about it, I apologize in advance. 

Background Info: 
I'm in the process of learning to code. I'm using freeCodeCamp as my main source of education for now. Currently, I'm working on the [personal portfolio project](https://learn.freecodecamp.org/responsive-web-design/responsive-web-design-projects/build-a-personal-portfolio-webpage) and what I'd like to do is separate my projects by focus and use icons to represent each focus. 

For the ""Responsive Web Design Projects, I was hoping Font-Awesome could create an icon for this? Like a Desktop Screen, Tablet, and Mobile grouped together?

### Example image (optional)

FlatIcon has _[something similar](https://www.flaticon.com/free-icon/responsive-design-symbol_65381)_ to what I'm looking for but they want full credit on the page itself instead of in the HTML/CSS sections. I want this page to eventually get better as I learn more (planning to use it to gain traction towards a job). I have no problem crediting but at the end of the day, it's going to junk-up my portfolio. 

### Icon request checklist

- [X ] This is a single icon or matched pair (Ex: `lock` / `unlock`)
- [X ] The title starts with ""Icon request: "" and is followed by the requested icon name (Ex: `Icon request: magical-unicorn`)
- [X ] I have [searched for existing issues](https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome/issues) and to the best of my knowledge this is not a duplicate
- [X ] I have included at least one example image if it could be helpful (optional)
- [X ] The request is for a concrete object (it's harder to make an icon to represent happiness, it's easier to make a smiley face. ☺)

Thanks in advance for any help you can provide. Again, if I did this wrong, my apologies. 

Amber",{},{}
