11089,IssuesEvent,2017-11-02 17:59:41+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,3008187,jmgirven,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,Push / append to list in Datastore,[],[],0,"I have a Datastore entity that represents a video that I am hosting. When this video is uploaded, a group of workers process different versions of the video, and when complete, append the processed version ID to a list in my entity. Something like:

```
# Get the entity
ds = datastore.Client()
query = ds.query(kind=VIDEO)
query.add_filter('video_id', '=', video_id)
entity = list(query.fetch(limit=1))[0]

# Add the processed version
entity['processed'].append(version_id)

# Save the entity
ds.put(entity)
```

Largely this is OK, but occasionally after all the processing is complete, the entity does not contain all the completed version IDs. I am wondering if this is because two processes are adding version IDs at the same time, one overwriting the other's data.

Instead of the above, in MongoDB I would use [$push](https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/update/push/) to append to the processed list. Is there something similar in Datastore? Or do I need to change my model to use a different structure?",{},{}
