11179,IssuesEvent,2016-02-02 20:26:27+00:00,11031844,uqfoundation/dill,10009354,disconnect3d,2855931,uqfoundation,opened,Dill fails on classes with __slots__,[],[],0,"By default dill fails to serialize objects/classes that contains `__slots__` (more about slots [here](https://github.com/yasoob/intermediatePython/blob/master/__slots__magic.rst)):
```python
class A(object):
    __slots__ = ['a']

import dill
dill.dumps(A)
```

with `RuntimeError: maximum recursion depth exceeded` - as far as I understand, it somehow tries to pickle `a` and think that it requires `A` and so tries to pickle it once again and so on.

`pickle` for example can do it.

The problem can be solved by passing `byref=True` to `dumps`, however I believe this shouldn't make any difference in such case.

If that can't be fixed anyhow, there should be at least an error similar to the one from `pickle` when trying to `pickle.dumps(A())`:
```TypeError: a class that defines __slots__ without defining __getstate__ cannot be pickled```

I've used dill 0.2.4 and Python 2.7.10.",{},{}
11180,IssuesEvent,2017-08-09 15:10:03+00:00,11031844,uqfoundation/dill,16778174,greyltc,2855931,uqfoundation,opened,PicklingError: Can't pickle : it's not found as mpmath.ctx_mp_python.constant,[],[],0,"python 3.6
steps to reproduce:
``` python
import dill
import mpmath
pi = mpmath.pi
dill.dumps(pi) # gives error
dill.dumps(pi, recurse=True) # also gives error
```
Is this possibly related to #104?",{},{}
