11460,IssuesEvent,2016-11-18 07:58:39+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,21322887,yscg,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Duplicated entries in resource file under CONCAT_TEXT mode,[],[],0,"We are using pants 1.2.0 and there are duplicated entries in a resource file under CONCAT_TEXT mode. 

I want to merge two java service implementation files using the CONCAT_TEXT mode. However, the merged file containing many duplicated entries.  Some definitions are as below:

```
resources (
    name = 'test-resource',
    sources = [
        'META-INF/services/java.util.Iterator'
    ]
)
jvm_binary(
    name = 'test',
    source = 'SOME_PATH/Test.java',
    dependencies = [
        ':test-resource'
        '3rdparty/..' # Some other module containing META-INF/services/java.util.Iterator 
    ],
    deploy_jar_rules=jar_rules(rules=[
        Duplicate('^META-INF/services/java.util.Iterator$', Duplicate.CONCAT_TEXT)
    ]),
    main = 'com.yscg.Test'
)
```
The `META-INF/services/java.util.Iterator` in `test-resource` containing one line:
`com.yscg.TestIterator`.
There are three lines of `com.yscg.TestIterator` in the generated `META-INF/services/java.util.Iterator` in the jar package. The problem still exists when the 3rdparty dependency is removed. 

The problem doesn't occur if the resource file is in the root directory. And from the debugging messages, we find there is a command named `org.pantsbuild.tools.jar.Main` with the following parameters:
```
-files  SOME_BUILD_PATH/META-INF=META-INF,SOME_BUILD_PATH/META-INF/services=META-INF/services,SOME_BUILD_PATH/META-INF/services/java.util.Iterator=META-INF/services/java.util.Iterator
```

I think the problem may be that the file was also copied when copying the parent directory. And The line was appended three times. We ran the command with only the root directory 
`-files  SOME_BUILD_PATH/META-INF=META-INF`, and that solved the problem. #",{},{}
