11467,IssuesEvent,2018-02-03 03:36:48+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,1883523,kwlzn,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,generalize `./pants repl.py` interpreter support,"[{'id': 378083067, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/python', 'name': 'python', 'color': 'c2e0c6', 'default': False}]",[],0,"currently, `./pants repl.py` provides support for ipython via an `--ipython` flag + two control args for the requirement and entrypoint here: https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/master/src/python/pants/backend/python/tasks/python_repl.py#L28-L33

however, it's possible to use this to readily inject other repls, like `bpython`:

```
[omerta pants (master)]$ ./pants -q repl.py --ipython --ipython-entry-point='bpython' --ipython-requirements=""['bpython']"" 3rdparty/python:psutil

bpython version 0.17 on top of Python 2.7.14 /opt/ee/python/2.7/bin/python2.7
>>> import psutil
>>> psutil.cpu_count(
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ psutil.cpu_count: (*args, **kwargs)                                                                      │
│ cpu_count                                                                                                │
│ Return the number of logical CPUs in the system (same as                                                 │
│ os.cpu_count() in Python 3.4).                                                                           │
│                                                                                                          │
│ If logical is False return the number of physical cores only                                             │
│ (e.g. hyper thread CPUs are excluded).                                                                   │
│                                                                                                          │
│ Return None if undetermined.                                                                             │
│                                                                                                          │
│ The return value is cached after first call.                                                             │
│ If desired cache can be cleared like this:                                                               │
│                                                                                                          │
│ >>> psutil.cpu_count.cache_clear()                                                                       │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

..so it would probably make sense to generalize the arg naming here a bit.

it would be interesting to figure out how to generalize a CLI ""mode"" (like `./pants repl.py --mode=ipython`) to map to a user-configurable tuple of (injectable_requirements, entrypoint) for each mode.

then you could have a `pants.ini` like:

```
[repl.py]
custom_repls: {
    'ipython': ('ipython==1.0.0', 'IPython:start_ipython'),
    'bpython': ('bpython==0.17', 'bpython'),
    # insert future repl here, as config
  }
```

to dynamically support various repls - including those that don't yet exist - as used by multiple users in a monorepo.
",{},{}
