11506,IssuesEvent,2016-07-27 21:49:13+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,`genrule` support via isolated processes,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/engine', 'name': 'engine', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],0,"Most of the pieces are now in place to implement something like `gen_rule` using the isolated process support, and there are consumers for whom we would immediately be able to get our foot in the door to clean up legacy orchestration code.

The missing link is between v1 Tasks (frontend) and v2 Tasks (backend): in particular:

1. How would a v1 Task create requests for products from the new engine (via `prepare`, most likely)?
2. In this case, the resulting product will likely be wrapped up in a Snapshot... how would the frontend task extract the snapshot (into `dist`, most likely)?

cc @baroquebobcat, @kwlzn, @JieGhost  ",{},{}
