11794,IssuesEvent,2016-03-25 20:19:28+00:00,8763405,SoCo/SoCo,6287596,pfischi,3826649,SoCo,opened,Error parsing AVTransport events when playing Deezer Tracks,[],[],0,"An error in event handling rountine occurs, when a Deezer track is played. This happens because of an unknown item class ""object.container.album.musicAlbum.#DEFAULT"" in the event xml string.

As a workaround, i've added a new class to ""data_structures.py"" to solve the problem.

`
class DidlMusicAlbumDefault(DidlAlbum):

    item_class = 'object.container.album.musicAlbum.#DEFAULT'
    tag = ''
    _translation = DidlAudioItem._translation.copy()
    _translation.update(
        {
            'artist': ('upnp', 'artist'),
            'genre': ('upnp', 'genre'),
            'producer': ('upnp', 'producer'),
            'toc': ('upnp', 'toc'),
            'album_art_uri': ('upnp', 'albumArtURI'),
        }
    )
`

With best regards,

Stefan",{},{}
11802,IssuesEvent,2017-06-13 12:22:48+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,13453618,harishbalachandran,3926525,learningequality,opened,Facility admin is able to delete his/her own user ID while logged in using the same ID.,[],[],0,"## Summary

Groups created does not get updated on real time on Learner group section and under exams section.

Instead we have to refresh the page to see the changes.

## System information
 - Version: Kolibri 0.4.0beta10
 - Operating system: Ubuntu 14.04 LTS
 - Browser: Chrome

## How to reproduce

1. Add groups move learners.
2. Navigate to Learners tab and check the groups column, the changes will not be seen.
3. Navigate to Exam tab and try to allocate to the group, the drop down will not have the group you crated.
4. But on refreshing the page once we are able to see these changes on both Learners tab and Exam allocation.

## Screenshots
Adding Group
