11806,IssuesEvent,2017-01-23 17:26:47+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,2367265,indirectlylit,3926525,learningequality,opened,allow SVG icons to be put in core and used across all apps,"[{'id': 492821376, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/DEV:%20frontend', 'name': 'DEV: frontend', 'color': 'DFDFDF', 'default': False}, {'id': 492816641, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/TASK:%20tech%20update', 'name': 'TASK: tech update', 'color': '996189', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Currently, we use a custom 'svg inliner' webpack loader to insert SVG into our vue templates. However, the loader is not leverage webpacks path resolution system, and so all SVG paths are relative to the current vue file.

This means that we have duplicated icons in every app; re-used icons should instead be available from core.

",{},{}
