11828,IssuesEvent,2018-03-27 21:41:11+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,374612,benjaoming,3926525,learningequality,closed,Centralize fetching KOLIBRI_HOME,"[{'id': 492822760, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/DEV:%20backend', 'name': 'DEV: backend', 'color': 'DFDFDF', 'default': False}, {'id': 492816641, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/TASK:%20tech%20update', 'name': 'TASK: tech update', 'color': '72486f', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'benjaoming', 'id': 374612, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/374612?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/benjaoming', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/benjaoming/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"### Observed behavior

There's currently a bug when using `~` in `KOLIBRI_HOME`. It was patched in the Debian pkgs in https://github.com/learningequality/kolibri-installer-debian/pull/24 -- the package contains a default configuration with `~`, so it was quite critical here. Other dists may not be as prone.

In #3128 the issue was partly fixed, but then because of a lack of guidance for using the ENV, I unfortunately repeated the mistake for `dbbackup` which fires automatically at upgrades.

The proper fix would be to unify all access in `kolibri.utils.conf`, one gotcha being that tests seem to mock the environment, therefore we should also fix this. I think we can read `KOLIBRI_HOME` just once and then adapt the tests for this behavior.

### Expected behavior

DRY in code, and no more errors with `~` not working.

### User-facing consequences

Broken upgrades if setting `KOLIBRI_HOME=~/.blah`

### Errors and logs

n/a

### Steps to reproduce

    KOLIBRI_HOME=""~/.kolibri"" kolibri manage dbbackup

### Context

0.8.0

",{},{}
