    self._token_embedder = _ElmoCharacterEncoder(options_file, weight_file, requires_grad=requires_grad)
  File ""/usr/local/lib/python3.6/site-packages/allennlp-0.5.2_unreleased-py3.6.egg/allennlp/modules/elmo.py"", line 279, in __init__
    self._options = json.load(fin)
  File ""/usr/local/lib/python3.6/json/__init__.py"", line 296, in load
    return loads(fp.read(),
  File ""/usr/local/lib/python3.6/codecs.py"", line 321, in decode
    (result, consumed) = self._buffer_decode(data, self.errors, final)
UnicodeDecodeError: 'utf-8' codec can't decode byte 0x89 in position 0: invalid start byte
```
I wrote a small reader for this file, and it runs fine.
I open and save the options file with 'utf-8' encoding to be sure.
I've tweaked the module sources to print how the option file was red and it gave me nonsense, as if the encoding wasn't right.
Even hard-coding `utf-8` as encoding or using byte mode (`rb`) in the `open()` call won't change a thing.

I really don't understand what's happening here.

**To Reproduce**

Steps to reproduce the behavior
1. Use fresh allennlp install from source with Dockerfile (only pandas installed on top)
2. Download weights and options file for 5.5B pre-trained version
3. Write some piece of code with an instance of ElmoEmbedder class with those files paths
