12582,IssuesEvent,2017-11-18 18:21:13+00:00,22757589,freelawproject/juriscraper,1270718,johnhawkinson,6012898,freelawproject,opened,Massachusetts appellate URL change,[],[],0,"Mass. has restructued its website as of a month or so ago, and new opinions are not being scraped.

It moved opinions from
  http://www.mass.gov/courts/court-info/sjc/about/reporter-of-decisions/new-opinions.html
to
  https://www.mass.gov/service-details/new-opinions.

Juriscraper was using an XML (RSS?) variant of the first page:
  http://www.mass.gov/courts/court-info/sjc/about/reporter-of-decisions/opinions.xml

https://github.com/freelawproject/juriscraper/blob/67dfee19e219cbf1f277b439ce2342c7bb68f53f/juriscraper/opinions/united_states/state/mass.py#L27

I don't know if that still exists at a new URL.

Note that some of this kinda lost to history forever because Mass slip opinions disappear after 14 days. They can be obtained via the free LEXIS site, but that formats them differently.
",{},{}
