12669,IssuesEvent,2015-11-11 15:56:23+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,73019,mboersma,6117407,deis,closed,Flannel doesn't start after reboot,[],[],3,"https://github.com/deis/deis/commit/445dbaecfadb1e2690734413cc43f30abcb13b21#diff-be438a7ce6a159afe476e6cb80c59eddR53

I had been using ""set"" instead of ""mk"" in my unit. I was updating my units to match the official Deis files and when I changed this to ""mk"" flannel wouldn't boot because this key was already set. I might be missing something, because I would think others would have run into this very fast. Might just be something unique in my setup.",{},{}
12677,IssuesEvent,2015-03-20 18:15:25+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,536009,carmstrong,6117407,deis,opened,Proposal: Admins can create new users,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/controller', 'name': 'controller', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],0,"We currently have the ability to [disable user registration](http://docs.deis.io/en/latest/managing_deis/operational_tasks/#disabling-user-registration) entirely, but a common scenario is that admin users want to be able to create users, but not allow just anyone from creating an account.

The proposal is to have three registration permission modes:
* Users can register themselves (the default)
* No users can register (`registrationEnabled`, which we currently have)
* Only admins can create user accounts (`registrationByAdminOnly` or something similar)

These could even be collapsed into one setting called something like `registrationMode`. ",{},{}
12686,IssuesEvent,2016-11-10 21:59:35+00:00,53438969,globus/globus-cli,3958448,corpulentcoffee,6120321,globus,closed,globus whoami output,"[{'id': 338347008, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-cli/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 455896809, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-cli/labels/usability', 'name': 'usability', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Removed the ""Logged in as: "" from the globus whoami output.

Currently its:
$ globus whoami
Logged in as: tuecke@uchicago.edu

Change it to:
$ globus whoami
tuecke@uchicago.edu

This makes it behave more consistently with the system whoami, and makes the output easier to parse and use.

For the verbose output, change the fields names to:

$ globus whoami -v
Username: tuecke@uchicago.edu
Name: Steven Tuecke
Id: b04b1e76-d274-11e5-bf36-07c9790e3d20
Email: tuecke@uchicago.edu

I.e., use ""Username:"" rather than ""Logged in as:""

When not logged in, change the error message to:

$ globus whoami
You are not logged in. Use 'globus login' to login.
",{},{}
12688,IssuesEvent,2018-06-22 21:21:38+00:00,53438969,globus/globus-cli,1300022,sirosen,6120321,globus,opened,"In v2, should we drop `--version` in favor of only supporting `globus version`?","[{'id': 671769634, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NzE3Njk2MzQ=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-cli/labels/breaking-change-requires-v2', 'name': 'breaking-change-requires-v2', 'color': 'b60205', 'default': False}, {'id': 338347011, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMzgzNDcwMTE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-cli/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': True}]",[],0,"I think I was the originator of having both options, and `globus version --version` has gotten its fair share of laughs.

In #420, I note that eager options have ""first one wins"" semantics, and that this can cause issues with `--version --verbose` evaluation.
This issue, and the silliness of `globus version --version` disappears if we drop the `--version` flag in v2.

There are other more involved solutions. e.g. `--version` could put a callback somewhere, and we could change command invocation to check for that callback before executing the function in question. Then the `--version` evaluation callback would execute to completion, stash a secondary callback, and exit. `--verbose` would evaluate, and only after option parsing we'd hit command invocation...
It seems like a very roundabout alternative to dropping `--version`.",{},{}
12693,IssuesEvent,2016-06-20 19:36:29+00:00,53344710,globus/globus-sdk-python,825586,bd4,6120321,globus,closed,"Require [general] section header in config, be standard INI","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-sdk-python/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],2,"Although it originally seemed like a nice bit of user-friendliness to not strictly require a section heading for the `[general]` section, it's causing grief in the CLI already ( globus/globus-cli#12 ).

Standard INI format requires that all sections have headers, so we should just move to that.
It does mean that any SDK users will get parsing errors if we do the upgrade harshly.

We should update tokens.globus.org , then tell people on the developer listhost that we're changing this and they should update.
Since the current parser tolerates full INI files, no one will have issues who listens to us.

After that's done, we're still in beta, so I think it will be safe to just drop the special parsing code.

@bda , thoughts?",{},{}
