13256,IssuesEvent,2016-11-03 20:56:43+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,16448634,derekbekoe,6844498,Azure,opened,Support rolling back from nightly build to public build in `az component`,"[{'id': 418968915, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Discussion', 'name': 'Discussion', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Whilst **it is recommended** to install nightly builds into a virtual environment, many install the nightly build into their global location and over the top of any other non-nightly installation they already have.

Currently, `az component` does not support rolling back to a previous version.

As suggested by @JasonRShaver, @tjprescott, it would be helpful to have support to rollback to the latest non-nightly/public version of the CLI.

A suggestion has been an `az component rollback` command.",{},{}
