13324,IssuesEvent,2017-11-02 12:28:54+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,9039085,snebel29,6844498,Azure,closed,Impossible to add route-table to subnet on different resource groups,[],[],1,"Hi,
I'm unsucessfully trying to update the route-table of a subnet, the subnet and the route table exists in different resource groups, I can do it using Azure portal but I can't do it using the CLI.

I've tried the following combination of commands

By using the resource group where the vnet exists
```
az network vnet subnet update \
    --resource-group ""vnet-rg"" \
    --vnet-name ""my-vnet"" \
    --name my-subnet \
    --route-table ""my-routetable""
```
By using the resource group where the route table exists
```
az network vnet subnet update \
    --resource-group ""route-table-rg"" \
    --vnet-name ""my-vnet"" \
    --name my-subnet \
    --route-table ""my-routetable""
```
By using the canonical adress id of the vnet
```
az network vnet subnet update \
    --route-table ""my-routetable"" \
    --ids ""/subscriptions/xxxxxxxxxxxxxx/resourceGroups/vnet-rg/providers/Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks/my-vnet/subnets/vnetname""
```

Always unable to find either the vnet or the route table

```
The Resource 'Microsoft.Network/routeTables/my-routetable' under resource group 'the-rg' was not found
```
Feels to me that the az cli tool should allow to perform this action since you can do it from the portal, is there any workaround?

### Environment summary

azure-cli (2.0.14) 

Thanks
",{},{}
13346,IssuesEvent,2017-11-30 17:37:24+00:00,4127088,Azure/azure-sdk-for-python,1050156,lmazuel,6844498,Azure,closed,msg.renew_lock() does not update the  broker_properties['LockedUntilUtc'],"[{'id': 117005107, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/labels/Feature', 'name': 'Feature', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}, {'id': 117005255, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/labels/Service%20Bus', 'name': 'Service Bus', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}]",[],10,"# Details: 

`Message` can be lock. This lock has `timeout`. The timeout can be found at `msg.broker_properties['LockedUntilUtc']`. But when one calls `renew_lock()` This field does not get an update 

## Possible solution: 

@lmazuel suggested to have `when_expire` function. On default it returns `LockedUntilUtc` but on successful `renew_lock` call it returns an update clock field.  


More info can be found at 
https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/pull/742
",{},{}
