14015,IssuesEvent,2018-05-04 03:53:05+00:00,1199632,schematics/schematics,17398258,yangyangxcf,7866441,schematics,opened,[Feature] Passing `role` to `atoms` in `export_loop`,[],[],0,"At present, `atoms` is used in `export_loop` to traverse all fields and serializables. Some serializables can be very time consuming, but we don't need them all the time because we may blacklist them in some roles. So I think it good not to get all fields and serializables in `atoms`, but only those who are not filtered by `role`.

As an example, to say I have a model  `shop`,
```python
class Shop(Model):
    id = IntType()
    name = StringType()

    class Option:
        roles = {
            'detailed': wholelist(),
            'default': blacklist('goods'),
        }

    @serializable
    def goods(self):
        return get_all_goods_from_shop_id(self.id)
```
I might query a database in `get_all_goods_from_shop_id` which is costly. I do not need it in the `default` role, however, it will still be computed during serialization.",{},{}
