14576,IssuesEvent,2017-10-20 15:02:21+00:00,26784827,dotnet/core,2228528,keithnicholson,9141961,dotnet,opened,.NET Core 2.0 Runtime on MacOS:  Error running dotnet,[],[],0,"# Issue Title

.NET Core 2.0 Runtime on MacOS:  Error running dotnet

# General

Good day!  I had a buddy with a Mac install the .NET Core 2.0 Runtime from:  

https://www.microsoft.com/net/download/core 

Chose the macOS (x64) PKG file.  It ran and we see  - 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The following was installed at /usr/local/share/dotnet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;•	Microsoft .NET Core Runtime - 2.0.0

However, when we go to a Terminal and type ""dotnet --version""  we get the following item:
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Did you mean to run dotnet SDK commands? Please install dotnet SDK from: http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=798306&clcid=0x409

we added ""sudo"" in front and got the same.

Have we missed something?

Best wishes,
Keith

",{},{}
