14723,IssuesEvent,2015-11-17 16:54:32+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,479213,pde,9289019,letsencrypt,closed,Nginx parser needs add_or_set_server_directives,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/labels/nginx', 'name': 'nginx', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],3,"Right now Nginx's parser has an add_server_directives method, with a `replace` parameter. If `replace` is true, the directive must already exist in the config, and it will be replaced. If `replace` is false, the directive is added regardless of what exists in the config.

Since most directives are not allowed repeatedly, what we want in many cases is an `add_or_set_server_directives`, which will replace a directive if it's present*, and add it if it's not present.

*To be really tidy, we should say: If the directive is present with the correct value, leave it alone, i.e. don't change its location in the config.",{},{}
