15080,IssuesEvent,2018-01-30 16:23:44+00:00,46293472,Backblaze/B2_Command_Line_Tool,12545953,mdp1,10283486,Backblaze,opened,b2 upload file is slow,[],[],0,"Using b2 cli within a backup script.
`b2 upload_file $BUCKET ""$path"" $DAILY_PATH/$filename`

```
# b2 version
b2 command line tool, version 1.1.0
```

When the backup script is run by cron I seem to consistently get very slow upload speeds (~100kB/s often less).  When the backup script is run directly I often see upload speeds of 1-3MB/s even when run at the same time as the cron is running so slowly. 

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12545953/35577413-c8c3b2ae-05e1-11e8-9a4f-40302488a55e.png)

I have seen other b2 cli issues where the upload speed is very slow if number of threads is 1 but gets faster with larger number of threads.  If `--threads` is not specified is there a default or does the b2 cli make a decision automatically which could lead to seeing such a big discrepancy in upload speed for 2 b2 uploads running at the same time?",{},{}
