15410,IssuesEvent,2016-01-04 22:11:03+00:00,21987374,django-json-api/django-rest-framework-json-api,224267,gonvaled,11215076,django-json-api,closed,Configure type inflection rules,[],[],3,"`EmberData` is `POST`ing:

```
    {
      ""data"": {
        ""attributes"": {
          ""name"": ""The project name"",
          ""description"": ""The project description"",
          ""price"": 123
        },
        ""relationships"": {
          ""onwer"": {
            ""data"": null
          }
        },
        ""type"": ""projects""
      }
    }
```

And `Django` (`django-rest-framework-json-api` I guess) is complaining with a `409 Conflict`:

```
    {
      ""errors"": {
        ""detail"": ""The resource object's type (projects) is not the type that constitute the collection represented by the endpoint (project).""
      }
    }
```

Apparently the `JSONApi` spec [does not][1] enforce an inflection rule. How can I tell `django-rest-framework-json-api` to accept plurals for the type?

  [1]: http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-resource-object-identification",{},{}
