Clicking the menu item leaves the cursor hovering above the topmost visible cell. The border around the active cell is removed as expected, though.

![screenshot 2017-02-04 23 02 10](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3074453/22621534/9f0d8eb8-eb2e-11e6-9783-a63b0c19b76d.png)


I wouldn't mind fixing this one myself. Probably something to do with `@media print` in [/static/style/main.css](https://github.com/nteract/nteract/blob/master/static/styles/main.css)?


PS: I think it's awesome that you can export pdfs where the cell input is hidden for plotting code. It looks nice :sparkles: ",{},{}
