15757,IssuesEvent,2018-02-21 20:48:55+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,6611546,theengineear,12401040,nteract,closed,Notebook types are wrong in @nteract/types/core/records,[],[],0,"I just noticed that flow wasn't actually resolving the types for the records because of two things:

* `@nteract/types/core/records` resolves to the lib version
* The flow definitions are not copied for the records

It's not a simple switch though -- as soon as I ""fixed"" that, I found an overwhelming amount of flow errors to get through. Most of the issue is that `Immutable.Map`s are not used for the notebook when they should be (up until we switch to `Immutable.Record` in `commutable`. Honestly though, the records should be relying on commutable's types if at all possible.
",{},{}
