15787,IssuesEvent,2018-04-20 02:05:06+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,26384082,stale[bot],12401040,nteract,closed,Add mime-type to stdout,"[{'id': 900078574, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nteract/nteract/labels/stale', 'name': 'stale', 'color': 'f9deac', 'default': False}]",[],4,"The Jupyter protocol seems like it assumes that stdout is always text, but there are cases where you'd like to have rich visualizations that are emitted throughout execution (not just at the end).

For example, TensorFlow visualizations are of binary blobs they call summaries. These summaries are emitted throughout execution (not just at the end). So they’re much more like print statements in other languages, which traditionally go to stdout.

i’m looking to do the same… have these summary blobs be visualized as they arrive, rather than just when the execution result is ready.

@rgbkrk You mused in Slack: ""I wonder if thats why stream output in colab has metadata 🤔 """,{},{}
