15854,IssuesEvent,2017-11-30 04:35:06+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,12214074,m1ghtym0,12520807,angr,opened,STT_GNU_IFUNC is relocated twice,[],[],0,"When I try to load a binary with `STT_GNU_IFUNC` relocations, they are
resolved when creating the project with all other relocations during
`self.initial_load_objects = self._internal_load(main_binary, *force_load_libs)`

At the end of the project creation, `simos.configure_project` is called.
Which triggers the ifunc resolution in

https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/fcf7d376505e53eaa878325fbf70d4c191416a98/angr/simos/linux.py#L81-L108

Since, the relocations are resolved alread, `funcaddr` is the resolved address and not the a ptr to the resolve stub.

This leads to an exception during runtime when the `IFuncResolver` `SimProcedure` is called.
",{},{}
