After a little research on forums, I found a similar error mentioning (below). Not sure if this is relevant, but I wanted to add it as a note.

``` The issue here is that recent versions of netCDF-C save the NC_CHAR dtype as fixed length UTF8 strings, which h5py cannot read. ```

",{},{}
