17182,IssuesEvent,2017-07-11 01:59:28+00:00,51442999,python-cmd2/cmd2,2812720,tleonhardt,17161025,python-cmd2,closed,Extraneous output from pyperclip on Linux when using Python 3 and xclip,"[{'id': 324131050, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-cmd2/cmd2/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'tleonhardt', 'id': 2812720, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/2812720?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/tleonhardt', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Currently when importing ``cmd2`` on Linux with Python3 when pyperclip is using xclip under the hood, there is some extraneous output when attempting the paste from an empty clipboard which says: ""Error: target STRING not available"".  

This output comes from the **xclip** command-line application and is occurring because when pyperclip calls xclip via a suprocess.Popen() call, it is redirecting stdout to a PIPE, but not stderr.

A workaround for now may be to do a ``pyperclip.copy('')`` instead of a ``pyperclip.paste()`` when using Python 3 on a Linux OS to determine if the clipboard functionality is working as intended.  This will have the disadvantage of overwriting whatever is in the clipboard when first starting up a cmd2 application, but it will at least get rid of the unnecessary and unwanted output.",{},{}
