17291,IssuesEvent,2016-09-04 12:25:26+00:00,10475159,django-ldapdb/django-ldapdb,694541,rbarrois,17748911,django-ldapdb,closed,ldapdb/tests.py will break in django 1.9,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/django-ldapdb/django-ldapdb/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]","[{'login': 'rbarrois', 'id': 694541, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/694541?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/rbarrois', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rbarrois/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",4,"The `Constraint` class from django's private API was deprecated in Django 1.7.
They replaced it with the public and documented `Lookup` class.
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.8/howto/custom-lookups/

`Constraint` will be completely removed in Django 1.9, and ldapdb/tests.py uses it a lot in the `WhereTestCase`. So to maintain compatibility, the tests needs to be majorly rewritten to test without using it.

Since Django no longer supports any versions before 1.7, it should not be necessary for the new testing approach to be compatible with versions older than that.",{},{}
