17634,IssuesEvent,2018-08-07 14:06:02+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,90851,palango,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Rename /transfers/* endpoint to /payments/*,[],"[{'login': 'palango', 'id': 90851, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjkwODUx', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/90851?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/palango', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/palango/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"## Problem Definition

In Tenerife we decided that a payment is **The process of sending tokens from one account to another. May be composed of multiple transfers (Direct or HTL). A payment goes from Initiator to Target.**

In #1949 we add a view into the payment history. This issue is to rename the current `'/transfers/<hexaddress:token_address>/<hexaddress:target_address>'` entpoint.

### ToDo:
- [ ] Rename `POST '/transfers/<hexaddress:token_address>/<hexaddress:target_address>'` to `POST '/payments/<hexaddress:token_address>/<hexaddress:target_address>'
- [ ] Update the docs
- [ ] Update the WebUI",{},{}
17641,IssuesEvent,2018-01-09 01:59:59+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,10471399,nkbai,19666847,raiden-network,opened,maker's lock expiration  when token swap,[],[],0,"for example
taker:
{
    ""role"": ""taker"",
    ""sending_amount"": 42,
    ""sending_token"": ""token1"",
    ""receiving_amount"": 76,
    ""receiving_token"": ""token2""
}
maker:
{
    ""role"": ""maker"",
    ""sending_amount"": 76,
    ""sending_token"": ""token2"",
    ""receiving_amount"": 42,
    ""receiving_token"": ""token1""
}

assume that maker and taker have direct channel on both token1 and token2
but token1's channel settle timeout is 600 
token2's channel settle timeout is 6000

In this scenario ,this token swap will fail because of lock expiration. 
but this token swap should be success.

how to rosolve:
1. maker set a short lock expiration :  
```
#lock_expiration = block_number + from_channel.settle_timeout
 lock_expiration = block_number +min(settle_timeout1 ,settle_timeout2)
```
2. taker set a short lock expiration
```
#lock_expiration = maker_paying_transfer.lock.expiration - raiden.config['reveal_timeout']
if ""maker_paying_transfer.lock.expiration  is too large"" :
     lock_expiration = block_number +min(settle_timeout1 ,settle_timeout2)
```
lines start with ""#"" are code copied from token_swap.py",{},{}
