17689,IssuesEvent,2017-03-31 22:07:57+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,Time out of running-icon?,"[{'id': 546254146, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/interactive%20UI', 'name': 'interactive UI', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}, {'id': 325435538, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/later', 'name': 'later', 'color': 'bfdadc', 'default': False}, {'id': 546253590, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/remote%20host', 'name': 'remote host', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}, {'id': 325435539, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/request', 'name': 'request', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Right now the running icon will run indefinitely even after the task engine has died. If it is not difficult, can we set a timer to the `fa-spin` class so that it would stop spinning after a while? The task engine would update the timer from time to time to keep it spinning if the task is actually running.",{},{}
17691,IssuesEvent,2017-05-17 17:25:19+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,tasks in the middle of step process.,[],[],0,"Currently a task starts from the `task` keyword and ends at the end of the step. I am wondering if there is a need for something like:

```
input: whatever
task:
   statement1
   statemetn2
task:
   another task
sh:
  a finalizing script.
```

This can currently be achieved with nested workflow, e.g.

```
[task1]
task:
   task1

[task2]
task:
   task2

[default]
input:
sos_run('task1')
sos_run('task2')
```

but I am not sure if the first style is more straightforward.",{},{}
17702,IssuesEvent,2017-02-23 13:48:11+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,917985,gaow,20074389,vatlab,closed,Separate Documentation and Tutorial tags,[],[],3,Currently we have both Documentation and Tutorials under the same tag `Documentation`. I think it would be easier to read if we separate them. ,{},{}
17704,IssuesEvent,2017-06-08 20:17:32+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Support for SAS kernel.,[],[],0,The biostat guys use SAS and R as two primary languages and sometimes need to mingle them. SAS has an [official Jupyter kernel](https://github.com/sassoftware/sas_kernel) so we should probably add SAS support soon.,{},{}
17708,IssuesEvent,2017-03-26 05:01:15+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,Setup a Travis CI test environment,"[{'id': 325435538, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/later', 'name': 'later', 'color': 'bfdadc', 'default': False}, {'id': 325435539, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/request', 'name': 'request', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}]",[],2,It takes quite a while to run all the tests now. It would be helpful if we could set up Travis CI to execute tests continuously for us.,{},{}
17709,IssuesEvent,2017-05-16 16:28:50+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,sos run -r without any additional parameter,[],"[{'login': 'BoPeng', 'id': 9889312, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/9889312?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/BoPeng', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"Currently `sos run -r` requires users to specify all previous parameters, and failure to do so will create a separate workflow and essentially disable `-r` (resume) mode. It makes sense to record the command of previous workflow and use `-r` to resume it.",{},{}
