18341,IssuesEvent,2018-02-16 00:45:10+00:00,35531022,opendatacube/datacube-core,108979,omad,26125288,opendatacube,closed,Fix for Ingestion of Existing Dataset Type Error,"[{'id': 210910442, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/opendatacube/datacube-core/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 838676436, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/opendatacube/datacube-core/labels/ingestion', 'name': 'ingestion', 'color': 'fc2a93', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'andrewdhicks', 'id': 15901813, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/15901813?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/andrewdhicks', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andrewdhicks/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",3,"In the ingestion script, the index is checked for an existing type and updates it if there are no 'bad' changes. The output type is set using [index.products.update](https://github.com/opendatacube/datacube-core/blob/develop/datacube/index/_datasets.py#L365) which has no return value, causing a NoneType error. Should the update function return a ProductResource or should the output type be updated in place without reassigning a value to output_type?

[Line, for quick reference](https://github.com/opendatacube/datacube-core/commit/f4b8b5dd2856530115afd8a3351b30c74344eb8d#diff-2a62009b43559ee82754f45d180200c6R153)",{},{}
18349,IssuesEvent,2017-05-31 23:29:54+00:00,35531022,opendatacube/datacube-core,15115493,Bis-Bala,26125288,opendatacube,reopened,TopologyException happens while loading data for a polygon region,[],[],2,"### Background

I'm using [agdc_statistics](https://github.com/GeoscienceAustralia/agdc_statistics) to process data from all of time for polygonal regions around Australia.

### Expected behaviour
The `datacube.utils.geometry.unary_union()` function is being used to `Union` the `valid_data` polygons from my source datasets (~1900), it should return a valid polygon for all of the sources.

The relevant line of code is:

`sources_union = geometry.unary_union(source.extent.to_crs(geobox.crs) for source in sources)`

### Actual behaviour
A `TopologyException` is raised instead of a valid shape being returned.

`ERROR 1: TopologyException: found non-noded intersection between LINESTRING (1.7e+06 -2.20922e+06, 1.7e+06 -2.23041e+06)
 and LINESTRING (1.7e+06 -2.3e+06, 1.7e+06 -2.2087e+06) at 1699999.9999999993 -2210399.5855833939`



### Steps to reproduce the behaviour
Perform a unary union on the valid data regions from these dataset ids: [datasetids.txt](https://github.com/opendatacube/datacube-core/files/1037347/datasetids.txt)

OR

Perform a unary union on these geometries: [source_geoms_wkt.txt](https://github.com/opendatacube/datacube-core/files/1037351/source_geoms_wkt.txt)

The exception occurs at [geometry.py#L644](https://github.com/opendatacube/datacube-core/blob/develop/datacube/utils/geometry.py#L644) which is a call to the underlying `ogr` library.

`union = geom.UnionCascaded()`


### Environment information

* Which ``datacube --version`` are you using?
    1.3.2 
* What datacube deployment/enviornment are you running against?
    Running on the NCI, loaded from `agdc-py3-prod`",{},{}
18353,IssuesEvent,2017-03-11 16:11:39+00:00,28841389,pyeve/eve-sqlalchemy,3992739,dkellner,26229868,pyeve,closed,projections not working,"[{'id': 163327723, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pyeve/eve-sqlalchemy/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],5,"## Problem

