18487,IssuesEvent,2017-12-31 15:56:03+00:00,8077625,python-gitlab/python-gitlab,1687888,gpocentek,28886265,python-gitlab,closed,Add support for subgroups,"[{'id': 706264816, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-gitlab/python-gitlab/labels/api:v4', 'name': 'api:v4', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}, {'id': 746307847, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-gitlab/python-gitlab/labels/feature', 'name': 'feature', 'color': 'f95e9c', 'default': False}]",[],0,"GitLab 10.3 introduces functionality to get a groups subgroups (https://docs.gitlab.com/ce/api/groups.html#list-a-groups-s-subgroups). I would like to have this supported in the Python API.

This functionality is quite essential, because in GitLab 10.3, it now only lists the 'root' groups with Gitlab.groups.list(all_available=True), so using the python-gitlab api it is no longer possible to get access to subgroups if you don't know their exact names.",{},{}
